OL,4,Cgrins as he is honoured on 100th
OL,5,Cbirthday
OL,7,FThe plumbing apprentice had been
OL,8,Fwalking home from college on February
OL,9,F2 1941 when air raid sirens started
OL,10,Fand he saw a German incendiary bomb
OL,11,Fland on the roof of City Hall.
OL,13,FRonald's son Ian Brignall said his
OL,14,F"modest" father had never spoken about
OL,15,Fhis wartime heroism and the family
OL,16,Fonly found out three months ago
OL,17,Fbecause he had kept some newspaper
OL,18,Fcuttings from the time.
