OL,4,Cgrins as he is honoured on 100th
OL,5,Cbirthday
OL,7,FShe thanked him for his "outstanding
OL,8,Fheroism" in tackling the blaze as
OL,9,F"other incendiary bombs and anti-
OL,10,Faircraft gunfire splinters were
OL,11,Ffalling around him".
OL,13,FRonald said: "I was only a teenager,
OL,14,Fand I didn't have any fear.
OL,16,F"I just wanted to make sure the bomb
OL,17,Fdidn't do any damage to City Hall."
OL,19,FAfter becoming an official fire-
OL,20,Fwatcher, he joined the RAF in 1944.
